  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Daily Temperatures\n\nFor each day, return how many days must pass before a warmer temperature appears. Use 0 when none appears.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: temperatures = [73, 74, 75, 71, 69, 72, 76, 73]\nOutput: [1, 1, 4, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: temperatures = [30, 40, 50, 60]\nOutput: [1, 1, 1, 0]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: temperatures = [60, 50, 40]\nOutput: [0, 0, 0]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Input sizes follow the original interview-style constraints.\n- Return values must match the described behavior.",
  "editorial": "Use a stack to keep unresolved items. When a new token, bar, or value resolves earlier items, pop them and update the answer.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def dailyTemperatures(self, temperatures):\n        result = [0] * len(temperatures)\n        stack = []\n        for i, temp in enumerate(temperatures):\n            while stack and temp > temperatures[stack[-1]]:\n                prev = stack.pop()\n                result[prev] = i - prev\n            stack.append(i)\n        return result\n```",
  "hints": [
    "A stack is useful when the most recent unresolved item should be handled first.",
    "Keep extra state on the stack when constant-time queries are needed."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def dailyTemperatures(self, temperatures):\n        pass\n"
  },
